div.p:
7. In order to assist in the disposal of this 270,000 tons, His Majesty’s Government would wish to know (a)
if they on their part should buy 100,000 tons per annum from Chile to replace a similar quantity released by the British Empire producers, would the U.S. Government for their part buy 170,000 tons: or, failing this, how much of the 170,000 tons would the U.S. Government be prepared to buy. (b)
if the U.S. Government are willing to undertake a joint copper buying policy in South America of this nature, (for the double purpose outlined in paragraphs (4) and (5) above) at what price the South American copper can be bought.
